function shuffleArray(array) {
  for (let i = array.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {
    const j = Math.floor(Math.random() * (i + 1));
    [array[i], array[j]] = [array[j], array[i]];
  }
}

let array = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];
shuffleArray(array);
console.log(array); 
// Prints [ 3, 5, 2, 1, 4] for example

This works by iterating through the array in reverse order, and for each item, randomly swapping that item with another randomly selected item earlier in the array

To achieve the desired result, you can modify the section identifier calculation logic to make the # section come at the end. Here's one way to do it:

1. Check if the first character of the fullName is a non-alphabet (using something like isalpha() function).
2. If it is, return a section identifier that is some value greater than the maximum ASCII value of any alphabet (for example, you can return a section identifier of '[' or '{').
3. If it is not, return the first character of the fullName as the section identifier.

So your code could look something like this:

<pre><code>NSString *sectionIdentifier;
NSString *firstChar = [[contactName substringToIndex:1] uppercaseString];

if (!isalpha([firstChar characterAtIndex:0])) {
    // non-alphabet character, use '[' as section identifier
    sectionIdentifier = @"[";
} else {
    sectionIdentifier = firstChar;
}

[newContact setValue:sectionIdentifier forKey:@"sectionIdentifier"];
[newContact setValue:contactName forKey:@"fullName"];
</code></pre>

And then use the following sort descriptor:

<pre><code>NSSortDescriptor *sortDescriptor = [NSSortDescriptor sortDescriptorWithKey:@"fullName"
        ascending:YES
        selector:@selector(localizedCaseInsensitiveCompare:)];
</code></pre>

This will sort the names case-insensitively, so that "Mary" and "mary" appear together. The section headers will also appear in the same order as the sort order, so the "#" section will come at the end.
